{
  "stem": "17761.6",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 24.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we used to eat some-- what food we had there, we ate together in the same dining hall.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then in 1948--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--Golda Meir came to Cyprus.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the Jewish Agency, who was the leading organization of the Jewish people at that time, they got a special authorization from the British to take out 10,000 children from the camps.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If I may be wrong with the number, if it's 10,000 or 8,000-- thousands of children.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she came to us to convince us that we should leave, let the Haganah determine a given number of people to go with that transport because they were interested in having soldier in Israel.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Her speech was unforgettable.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was in Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She was then carried like the pope.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we loved her.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I-- since then, I loved her.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And these transports started to organize.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So in-- in order to-- to earn a place that I could take as a [HEBREW], as a counselor-- I was young-looking-- younger than today at that time.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So they shaved me, and they shaved my legs and everything, and they gave me some short pants.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I became this youngster of [INAUDIBLE] that I told you before.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I went as a child to-- to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I arrived-- How old were you supposed to be?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I arrived-- I arrived the 31st of March or April 1, 1948-- about six, seven weeks, because before, the state of Israel has been established.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I arrived to Tel Aviv, which was already under Jewish administration.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The port of Tel Aviv couldn't even take in such a big ship.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It didn't-- a big ship that we were transported.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so we were shipped by little boats from the ship to the coast.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
